items.name: Alf - SDXL LoRA - (Dreambooth Trained)
items.description:
High Quality SDXL LoRA of the 1980s television star, Alf. The LoRA was extracted from an SDXL Dreambooth trained model created using 16 high quality images from the TV show and promos.

Trigger with "Alf Person" ("Alf" w/o the "Person" class token may work well also).

I'd recommend the DPM++2 (and 3) sampler series over the old default v1.4/5 samper "Euler_a" (for this model and for SDXL in general - makes a difference on my end)

You'll probably have to play w/ weighting to find a good balance of the LoRA vs. your prompt. Using .8 for the main value seems to work well with short prompts (see samples where .8 was used often).

SDXL training is a new thing so if I can make improvements I'll post additional versions.

If you enjoy this model post some images! Getting positive feedback is motivating to train/upload other models.

items.name: ComfyUI - Hybrid w Style Selector Workflow
items.description:
This workflow is tidy and fairly compact. I did my best to keep it as clean as possible. It includes the style selector and a couple of Efficiency Nodes. You can add up to four loras (or have ZERO loras if you prefer - for no Loras just leave the drop down menu at "none").

For this workflow to work you need to have "SDXL Prompt Styler" installed: https://github.com/twri/sdxl_prompt_styler as well as "Efficiency Nodes": https://github.com/LucianoCirino/efficiency-nodes-comfyui So you'll need to do that first if you want the workflow to work. I know it's a pain to have to download other things, but the style selector and Efficiency Nodes are worth the effort, IMO! :)

I also highly recommend the "ComfyUI-Manager": https://github.com/ltdrdata/ComfyUI-Manager.git If you're missing any nodes it will let you know which ones you're missing and will give you a quick one-click install option for the missing nodes.

The ZIP includes a style expansion for the SDXL Prompt Styler that adds over 70 art styles. Please read the included READ ME for usage tips! :)

If you have a minute after testing this out, please leave a rating! And if you enjoy this or get some creative fun out of it please consider donating: https://ko-fi.com/divaai It would really help to keep me making more assets for the AI community!

~ Diva

items.description:
If you like what I do please consider supporting me on Patreon and contributing your ideas to my future projects!

Glitter body paint is a captivating and visually striking form of artistic self-expression. This trend involves applying vibrant and shimmering body paint infused with fine glitter particles onto the skin. The result is a dazzling and ethereal appearance that catches the light and creates a sparkling effect as the wearer moves. Glitter body paint can be used to accentuate the contours of the body, highlight features, and create intricate designs or patterns. This style is popular at music festivals, parties, photo shoots, and other events where individuals seek to stand out and embrace their creative side. Whether used subtly for a touch of glamour or extravagantly for a bold statement, glitter body paint adds a touch of magic and whimsy to personal style.


Weight: ~ 0.8 (Higher if using a more complex prompt, anime styles can go lower)
CFG: ~ 7
Trigger: glitt3r
Additional tags: Black background
Clip skip: 1 - 2

I just wanted a model that could generate high quality art and hentai and that actually followed the damn prompt. Couldn't find one so I made one myself. Hope you like it and share your generations with everyone!

I hope this model becomes one of the last gems of the SD 1.5 era among other incredible trained models and merges, and not just another pointless mix that no one will ever use. But I know it's not easy to shine being so late and with so many popular models around.

If images are not reproducible, you can blame the software for being buggy and inconsistent

Using the model

Prompt

best quality,

I like to keep the filler tags to a minimum. Use danbooru tags or sentence-based prompts

Extension for tag autocompletion tagcomplete

Prompt Order for good composition

Tags at the start have more influence than the ones at the bottom.

The 7 blocks template WIP:

  1. view angle, sexual positions, sex acts,

  2. participants ->1girl, 1boy,

  3. posture, secondary actions,

  4. body -> breasts size, body fat, age, stature, body part focus,

  5. clothing

  6. hair color, hair style, eyes, cum location,

  7. location, furniture, objects,

You don't need to fill in every category, it's just for reference.

Negative prompt

worst quality, low quality, normal quality,

And whatever you don‚Äôt want to be on the image

Samplers

I like DPM++ SDE Karras but you can use any sampler.

TLDR: samplers that include an a (like euler a, DPM++ 2Sa Karras, etc) change the image with every step. Samplers like SDE will get to a fixed, more detailed result after ~30 steps. But any sampler can make detailed images by using Hires fix or upscaling.

Steps

25-50

You can go further but at that point I‚Äôd rather just make 2 images at 30 steps than one at 60

CFG

  • 7: standard

  • 3‚Äì15: working range

Lower cfgs don‚Äôt follow the prompt as much. Higher cfgs will make ‚Äúburned‚Äù images

The extension sd-dynamic-thresholding can play around with different CFGs at different steps

Sizes

  • 1:1¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† [512, 512], [768, 768]

  • 2:3¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† [512, 768]

  • 3:2¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† [768, 512]

For larger images, just generate them at normal size and use Hires fix or Upscale them

VAE

It's just the default 1.5 VAE, AKA. vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned

Permissions

  • Just use the model and share your generations here or wherever you want

  • I‚Äôd appreciate if you link to this model page when sharing your generations üòä

  • I made a patreon if you want to support me https://www.patreon.com/TianChimp

Please share your generations!

Tag considerations

I've noticed some tags having too much influence over the entire image resulting in a loss of style and quality, so I'd recommend setting lower influence with parentheses IE 0.5 - 0.8. Needs more testing but I'll keep a list of potential suspects.

  • fellatio -> oral, (fellatio:0.7),

Shown landscape images are upscaled to 1440 * 960 with img2img and same prompt, different seed, and denoising strength 0.55

No loras were used in the above images. Actually I haven't tested many, I'd guess you need to use fairly low weight on them because of the nature of the model.

ControlNetXL (CNXL) - A collection of Controlnet models for SDXL

Good news everybody - Controlnet support for SDXL in Automatic1111 is finally here!

This collection strives to create a convenient download location of all currently available Controlnet models for SDXL. If you are the author of one of these models and don't want it to appear here, please contact me to sort this out. The naming scheme of the files follows lllyasviel's from here https://huggingface.co/lllyasviel/sd_control_collection/tree/main.

Requirements for Automatic1111: at least version 1.5.0, better upgrade to the latest version of 1.6.0. + sd-webui-controlnet extension v0.400+. This is all still very new, so bugs or weird behaviour might occur. If you encounter any irregularities you can join us on our discord and ask for support or get in contact with the developers of Automatic1111/Controlnet via github/huggingface.

Known issues:

  • kohya-ss' controlnet lllite models seem to only have an effect when used with resolutions that are dividable by 16. supposed to be fixed in 1.1.410

  • currently there is no preprocessor for the blur model by kohya-ss , you need to prepare images with an external tool for it to work. there is now a preprocessor called gaussian blur.

  • As files with the extension .pth can't be uploaded the ip-adapter.pt from h94 has to be renamed manually after downloading.

  • The two versions of the control-loras from Stability.ai are marked as fp32/fp16 only to make it possible to upload them both under one version.

  • There have been reports especially for the control-loras to sometimes produce garbage when using scaled-dot-product cross optimization, xformers seems to be the better choice for them.

  • Deforum + Controlnet seems to break with the latest update of Automatic1111. Until a fix arrives you can downgrade to 1.5.2. seems to be fixed with latest versions of Deforum and Controlnet extensions.

A huge thanks to all the authors, devs and contributors including but not limited to: the diffusers institution, h94, huchenlei, lllyasviel, kohya-ss, Mikubill, SargeZT, Stability.ai, TencentARC and thibaud.

items.name: KureNaiZ - Artist Style
items.description:
If you enjoyed this model, why don't you check out my other works? I put a lot of effort into correctly recreating artist styles and making the occasional character LoRA.üòä

This model was trained using the collab/guide by holostrawberry [Guide] Make your own Loras, easy and free - colabs | Stable Diffusion Other | Civitai

Checkpoint used in examples:

model.ckpt ¬∑ a1079602570/animefull-final-pruned at main (huggingface.co)

The model was suggested by @NoriLilim.

I am once again open for suggestions for other styles, SFW and NSFW.

You can always drop model suggestions in the comments, both for styles that are missing on civit or those that are outdated.

About the artist:

Twitter: KureNaiZÁ¥Ö (Commission : Closed) (@KureNaiZ1) / X (twitter.com)

This artist makes ecchi to explicit art mostly depicting their original characters or characters from Honkai/Genshin. More nsfw images generally are rough sketches.

Women tend to be really thick or plump and there is a recognizable shine to their skin.

Weights & Prompts

The only necessary prompt is:

KureNaiZ

Adding "sketch" can help making the rougher, limited in color, image style as can be seen in the examples. This part of the model is a lot more volatile than the basic image generation.

Use a weight of 0.6-1.0, adjust to taste and depending on your checkpoint.

As usual I have included an XYZ plot for reference. The higher weights make the model break down completely so I recommend staying at 1.0 or lower.

As usual for models with little to no background art it fundamentally alters the layout for specific seeds but doesn't have a different style. Colorization and detailing is barely affected.

Please leave a review if you enjoyed this model or have problems with it. This helps me with improving future models and finetuning them in general. Give it a try and throw some images down below! üëá

items.name: AllWorkForkRowk_InProgress_(SD2.1)
items.description:
Still a work in progress.

Important 1: despite being a SD768, it was fine-tuned by me for countless epochs and steps on 512 ratios, this because it would've taken way shorter time, so now it's recommended to use hires fix (all images uploaded used latent nearly-exact)

Important 2: use the embeddigs listed for best results, decent results can be reached with normal negative prompts but i want you to get good results with the least hardship.

The first version (Alpha) is quite underfit because is a merge of two parallel fine-tunings (i used the Tensor-Merge of the SuperMerger Auto1111 extension), the prompt understanding is a bit lackluster and it is too on the second version (Beta).

The second version (Beta) has better fitting and the images generated are less blurry even with lower CFG.

The third version (Gamma) was made with a way higher LR (1e-5 on top of the previous 2e-6) and because of this it may be less stable and requires more testing, but anyway it seems to work nicely with an overall improvement, both on the understanding of prompts and quality of outputs, the only issue encountered yet is that the VG characters i trained it on seem to be overfit on their appearance.

modelVersions.name: V0.2_Gamma_(FasterLR)_512
modelVersions.description: Overall improvement, overfitting in the characters it had learned about, I'll fix it later and provide the list of the characters.

modelVersions.name: V0.1_Beta_512
modelVersions.description: Less underfit, remember to use the embeddings and if you are confused as to why it's 512 when it's listed 768, it's because I took a base 768 and fine-tuned on 512 ratio for speed.

modelVersions.name: V0_Alpha_tunedAt512
modelVersions.description: This version technically is 768x768 of 2.1, but it was heavily fine tuned on 512x512 ratio because I needed to work on it faster, because of this works best with hires fix, all listed images use the basic upscaler latent near-exact at 55% denoising

items.name: Norman (The Promised Neverland)
items.description:
If you enjoyed this LoRA, please hit the like button and give it a 5-star rating. Your encouragement motivates me to keep creating LoRAs like this.

Model used: AbyssOrangeMix3

Recommended VAE: orangemix or kl-f8

Trigger words: norman, neverland

On all images from preview I used DPM++ 2M SDE sampler, but you can use what you like.

Upscaler :

  • Detailed illust ‚Üí Latenet (nearest-exact)
    Denoise strength: 0.5 (0.5~0.6)

  • Simple upscale: Swin IR, ESRGAN, Remacri etc‚Ä¶
    Denoise strength: Can be set low. (0.35~0.6)

This LoRA was made using my new Dataset Automaker, which automatically make a dataset of 345 images for me from original anime screencaps.

Download dataset of 345 images to train your own LoRA:

https://drive.google.com/file/d/17TpO4GhWaig3QYjPBCodGUpaP1dg8K5i/view?usp=sharing
